{
  "texts": [
    "There are a number of different approaches to these models.",
    "Some of them include: word co-occurrence models in image grids, automated translation models that turn blobs of images into words, statistical models that do the same, topic models that look at both words and blobs, the Cross-media Relevance Model [43] which delves into the Continuous-space Relevance Model [44], and a combined distribution of words and image blobs, which prioritizes semantic features over visual ones like texture, form, and color.",
    "According to Zheng,Zhang,and Chen [45], it is proposed to enhance supervised Latent Dirichlet Allocation by including the hidden spaces of picture annotation and image classification.",
    "This is based on the assumption that there is a potential relationship between the labels and tags.",
    "By extending Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA) with a kernel, Melzer,Reiter,and Bischof [46] are able to bring data from the visual semantics, tags, and attributes domains into a shared subspace."
  ]
}